text: University of Warwick (pronounce as WORR-ik) is a British university. It is near Coventry, England between the West Midlands and Warwickshire. It is organised into three faculties — Arts (humanities); Science, Engineering and Medicine; and Social Sciences. There are 32 departments. In 2019, Warwick had about 26,531 full-time students and 2,492 academic and research staff. "People – University Profile – The University of Warwick". University of Warwick. 15 March 2015.
